WEBVTT

00:01.262 --> 00:03.438
Can I crash here tonight?

00:03.481 --> 00:05.962
You kept it?
Yeah.

00:06.006 --> 00:08.573
Jesus!
This is my mom, Meredith.

00:08.617 --> 00:10.140
What are you working on?

00:10.184 --> 00:12.055
A show I have coming up.

00:12.099 --> 00:14.144
You know,
if you're really interested,

00:14.188 --> 00:15.885
I'll be running the whole thing
out of the office here,

00:15.928 --> 00:18.105
and I am always looking
for smart people.

00:18.148 --> 00:19.584
Sure. Yeah.

00:19.628 --> 00:21.151
Thank you...Mm-hmm.

00:21.195 --> 00:22.805
...Pam.

00:22.848 --> 00:25.112
You're welcome...mm...

00:25.155 --> 00:28.289
There's a hippie compound
out in Laguna Beach.

00:28.332 --> 00:30.073
They're sitting on
a ton of cash.

00:30.117 --> 00:31.857
Should be easy.

00:33.076 --> 00:34.469
Yo. [ Grunts ]

00:36.210 --> 00:37.298
Alright, let's go!

00:37.341 --> 00:39.169
[ Gunshot fires ]Ah! Shit!

00:39.213 --> 00:40.257
[ Rapid gunfire ]

00:40.301 --> 00:41.650
You know who didn't
get busted?

00:41.693 --> 00:42.912
Your boyfriend.

00:42.955 --> 00:44.435
So either he's working
with the cops

00:44.479 --> 00:47.308
or it's easier for someone
to think that he is, right?

00:47.351 --> 00:48.309
[ Gunshot fires ]

00:48.352 --> 00:49.310
[ Thud ]

00:49.353 --> 00:50.876
Pope: This is new for you,
right?

00:50.920 --> 00:52.835
Deran: I thought I'd feel
something, but I don't.

00:52.878 --> 00:54.141
I don't feel anything.

00:54.184 --> 00:55.925
Pope: She has cancer.

00:55.968 --> 00:58.014
She won't let me
tell my brothers.

00:58.058 --> 01:00.016
I was supposed to pick up
my grandmother.

01:00.060 --> 01:02.018
She cut her chemo short
today.

01:03.367 --> 01:06.936
♪♪

01:06.979 --> 01:12.855
♪ She stares deeply

01:12.898 --> 01:16.728
♪ Locked inside me

01:16.772 --> 01:20.036
♪ Burnin' brightly

01:22.778 --> 01:28.392
♪ One they know
that I cannot take ♪

01:28.436 --> 01:31.874
♪ Waitin' for it all to begin

01:31.917 --> 01:35.312
♪ Every night now, they'll win

01:38.924 --> 01:41.536
♪ Come and meet my black hole

01:41.579 --> 01:45.496
♪ Got a big black hole

01:45.540 --> 01:49.370
♪ Got a big black hole

01:49.413 --> 01:53.156
♪ I've got a big black hole

01:53.200 --> 01:57.334
♪ I've got a big black,
big black hole ♪

01:57.378 --> 02:01.338
♪ Got a big black hole
inside of me ♪

02:01.382 --> 02:02.644
♪ Got a

02:03.993 --> 02:09.999
♪♪

02:13.611 --> 02:16.179
Adrian: I got caught.
Working for Jack.

02:16.223 --> 02:21.053
♪♪

02:21.097 --> 02:25.101
They told me I was gonna go
to jail for 20 years.

02:25.145 --> 02:28.148
The DEA said that
if I worked with them

02:28.191 --> 02:30.889
they could reduce
the charges.

02:30.933 --> 02:32.848
I could even get probation.

02:37.026 --> 02:39.071
I was -- I was supposed to
be done after Japan.

02:39.115 --> 02:42.597
And then, um,
this detective shows up,

02:42.640 --> 02:44.599
and he, uh,

02:44.642 --> 02:47.950
starts asking questions
about you and your brothers.

02:47.993 --> 02:52.215
Saying if I don't cooperate,
then the deal's off the table.

02:52.259 --> 02:58.569
♪♪

02:58.613 --> 03:04.967
♪♪

03:05.010 --> 03:08.100
I told them I don't
know anything, Deran.

03:08.144 --> 03:12.453
♪♪

03:12.496 --> 03:13.628
[ Sniffles ]

03:13.671 --> 03:16.892
♪♪

03:16.935 --> 03:18.633
Please. Say something.

03:18.676 --> 03:25.596
♪♪

03:25.640 --> 03:27.076
Deran?

03:27.119 --> 03:33.125
♪♪

03:35.345 --> 03:41.351
♪♪

03:43.353 --> 03:49.359
♪♪

03:51.535 --> 03:57.541
♪♪

04:03.547 --> 04:05.636
You didn't come in
last night.

04:07.377 --> 04:09.814
I came home late.

04:14.384 --> 04:16.865
Smurf was pretty sick.

04:21.216 --> 04:24.133
Are you gonna be the
one who ends up having
to take care of her?

04:26.091 --> 04:28.442
Yeah.
Of course it'll be you.

04:28.485 --> 04:29.791
Who else would do it?

04:31.358 --> 04:34.404
Do you know
what she wants?

04:34.448 --> 04:38.190
Does she want to be on
any kind of life support?

04:38.234 --> 04:40.454
Feeding tube?

04:40.497 --> 04:42.978
Ventilator?

04:43.021 --> 04:48.331
Did she sign anything to tell
you what to do when it gets bad?

04:48.375 --> 04:50.072
♪♪

04:50.115 --> 04:52.422
Because it's --
it's going to get bad.

04:52.466 --> 04:54.990
♪♪

04:55.033 --> 04:56.731
Meredith:
I know they want all access,

04:56.774 --> 04:58.341
but they aren't
gonna get it.

04:58.385 --> 04:59.690
Tacara:
What should I tell them?

04:59.734 --> 05:01.692
Tell them
that the eyebrow lady

05:01.736 --> 05:04.347
for the fifth most important act
on the bill

05:04.391 --> 05:07.089
is lucky we're giving her a meal
and a chair.

05:07.132 --> 05:09.918
Ah. The gentleman
courting my daughter.

05:09.961 --> 05:11.702
Are we being too loud?

05:11.746 --> 05:14.357
Is this for the show?

05:14.401 --> 05:16.577
Making sure everyone
has the right credentials,

05:16.620 --> 05:19.144
wristbands,
the whole nine yards.

05:19.188 --> 05:21.712
Oh, it says they also
want eyebrow lady

05:21.756 --> 05:23.323
to have limo service.

05:23.366 --> 05:26.326
No. She can park with the staff
like everyone else.

05:26.369 --> 05:29.503
Is waxing
even a talent?

05:29.546 --> 05:32.288
♪ I'd had some drinks
and couldn't get pulled over♪

05:32.332 --> 05:35.509
Hey, is this an 8,
or is it a 6?

05:35.552 --> 05:37.772
It's a 6.
Thank you.

05:37.815 --> 05:39.687
I do not understand
why smart people

05:39.730 --> 05:40.862
have such shitty
handwriting.

05:40.905 --> 05:43.081
[ Laughs ]

05:43.125 --> 05:44.735
What are you doing?

05:44.779 --> 05:46.433
Getting dressed.

05:46.476 --> 05:47.608
Are you leaving?

05:47.651 --> 05:49.479
No. Your mom said
I could help her

05:49.523 --> 05:52.395
with some of the prep work
for the festival.

05:52.439 --> 05:53.614
Right now?

05:53.657 --> 05:56.443
Yeah, I-I asked.

05:56.486 --> 05:59.359
[ Scoffs ]
Unbelievable.

05:59.402 --> 06:01.317
She is terrified
of getting old

06:01.361 --> 06:05.147
so she tries to make
all of my friends her friends.

06:06.670 --> 06:10.761
You know working with my mom's
not gonna get you any points.

06:10.805 --> 06:12.807
I already like you.

06:12.850 --> 06:15.070
It's cool.
I want to.

06:17.551 --> 06:20.162
So you'd rather stuff envelopes
for Meredith

06:20.205 --> 06:22.730
than have sex with me?

06:22.773 --> 06:24.384
Can't I do both?

06:24.427 --> 06:25.950
You're so lame.

06:27.865 --> 06:29.563
[ Chuckles ]

06:29.606 --> 06:31.260
[ Drill whirring ]

06:37.048 --> 06:39.007
What you doing?

06:39.050 --> 06:42.619
You know,
these asshole instructions

06:42.663 --> 06:44.665
said not to use a drill.

06:44.708 --> 06:46.884
It's taken like 3 hours
to do that side

06:46.928 --> 06:48.930
and like 10 minutes
to do this one.

06:48.973 --> 06:51.193
Did you get any sleep
at all?

06:51.236 --> 06:52.934
How much coke
did you do?

06:52.977 --> 06:56.633
[ Clears throat ]
I only did a bump.

06:56.677 --> 06:57.895
Mm-hmm.

06:57.939 --> 06:59.810
Sure you did.
Mm-hmm.

06:59.854 --> 07:02.465
What's this?

07:02.509 --> 07:04.293
It's a crib.

07:04.336 --> 07:07.862
Kid's gonna need a place
to sleep, right?

07:07.905 --> 07:12.519
Got like 5 stars on some
mom's website or some shit.

07:12.562 --> 07:14.477
You're reading
mom websites now?

07:14.521 --> 07:16.131
Well, yeah.

07:16.174 --> 07:18.089
I wanted to see how the baby
was breathing in your stomach,

07:18.133 --> 07:21.179
and then before you know it,

07:21.223 --> 07:24.879
I'm looking up, like,
crib safety and breast pumps.

07:24.922 --> 07:26.184
Breast pumps?

07:26.228 --> 07:27.708
I actually have
some recommendations.

07:27.751 --> 07:29.231
Oh, I'm sure you do.
I do.

07:29.274 --> 07:34.497
You know, it's all about suction
intensity and how it fits.

07:34.541 --> 07:36.020
Yeah.

07:37.587 --> 07:40.503
This is real, huh?

07:40.547 --> 07:42.070
I'm having a baby.

07:44.289 --> 07:45.508
Yeah.

07:49.425 --> 07:50.600
Hey.

07:50.644 --> 07:52.428
You're gonna do great.

07:56.258 --> 07:58.652
[ Indistinct conversations ]

08:06.224 --> 08:09.227
[ James Ervan Parker's
"Back to the Country" plays ]

08:11.012 --> 08:13.101
We've been here too long.

08:15.625 --> 08:17.279
We're a man down.

08:19.107 --> 08:20.717
He looks fine to me.

08:20.761 --> 08:22.327
Yeah.

08:22.371 --> 08:23.851
♪ Put your feet to the sole,
my friends♪

08:23.894 --> 08:26.680
♪ And remember
those hobnail boots♪

08:26.723 --> 08:30.422
♪ Jump around
in the mud again♪

08:30.466 --> 08:33.904
♪ Now, ain't it fine
gettin' back to the roots♪

08:33.948 --> 08:37.255
Any chance
we'll be productive today?

08:37.299 --> 08:38.953
Well, I'm taking
everyone's money.

08:38.996 --> 08:40.910
I'd say that's being productive.
[ Laughs ]

08:40.955 --> 08:42.870
-Yeah, first time ever.
-Come on, man.

08:42.913 --> 08:44.654
You don't like
dominoes?

08:44.698 --> 08:47.352
I don't play games.

08:47.396 --> 08:50.138
Let me know if anyone decides
to do anything useful.

08:50.181 --> 08:52.836
♪ Get on back♪

08:52.880 --> 08:53.750
♪ Get on...♪

08:53.794 --> 08:55.970
[ Footsteps ]

08:56.013 --> 08:58.712
[ Door creaks ]

09:05.240 --> 09:07.590
Thought you might want
some tea.
[ Gasps ]

09:10.637 --> 09:13.553
Get out of my room.

09:13.596 --> 09:15.685
Peppermint.

09:15.729 --> 09:18.688
It's good for nausea.

09:18.732 --> 09:22.649
I figured that's why
you're sleeping so late.

09:22.692 --> 09:25.216
My dad did two rounds
of chemo.

09:25.260 --> 09:27.088
Could barely
get out of bed.

09:28.872 --> 09:32.006
Dick cancer,
biggest dick I knew.

09:34.138 --> 09:39.883
I'll give you $10,000
to disappear for good.

09:39.927 --> 09:41.972
That's your number, huh?

09:42.016 --> 09:44.801
Solve anything
with 10 grand.

09:44.845 --> 09:46.847
You know, Julia never knew
when you were coming,

09:46.890 --> 09:48.849
but it always seemed to happen
when she was at her lowest.

09:48.892 --> 09:50.633
How about 15?

09:50.677 --> 09:53.593
How much did it take
the last time, Smurf?

09:53.636 --> 09:54.681
Huh?

09:54.724 --> 09:57.466
Did you up it
because I was in jail?

09:57.509 --> 10:00.861
20? 30?

10:00.904 --> 10:03.690
How much did it take
to kill her?

10:03.733 --> 10:06.910
$15,000.

10:06.954 --> 10:09.304
That is my final offer.

10:12.873 --> 10:14.831
Try the tea.

10:14.875 --> 10:16.964
It works.

10:17.007 --> 10:19.662
Let me know
if you need anything else.

10:27.104 --> 10:29.063
[ Seagulls squawking,
indistinct talking ]

10:29.106 --> 10:31.152
[ Dog barking ]

10:33.328 --> 10:35.547
I'm glad
you finally called.

10:37.811 --> 10:39.769
I can't do this.

10:39.813 --> 10:41.510
Charge me.

10:43.947 --> 10:46.863
Is that what you want me
to tell Livengood?

10:46.907 --> 10:48.822
I don't care
what you tell him.

10:48.865 --> 10:51.389
I'm done doing this with you
and with him.

10:51.433 --> 10:53.696
If that means that I go
to prison, then I go.

10:53.740 --> 10:57.831
♪♪

10:57.874 --> 11:03.271
Pretty boy like you
won't last six months in prison.

11:05.447 --> 11:07.841
You're young
and in love.

11:07.884 --> 11:09.756
I get it.

11:09.799 --> 11:13.455
But you have to
ask yourself,

11:13.498 --> 11:16.719
would Deran give all of this up
for you?

11:16.763 --> 11:21.942
♪♪

11:21.985 --> 11:24.771
Hey, J.
Does Smurf have a will?

11:24.814 --> 11:26.076
[ Vehicle door closes ]What?

11:26.120 --> 11:27.469
She's dying.

11:27.512 --> 11:29.297
We need to know where
all her money is going.

11:29.340 --> 11:31.603
How do you know
she's dying?
Pope told me.

11:31.647 --> 11:33.301
She won't let him
tell the others.

11:33.344 --> 11:35.869
Does she have a-a will?
A-A lawyer?

11:35.912 --> 11:37.305
I don't know.

11:37.348 --> 11:39.089
[ Sighs ] I'm trying
to get it out of Pope,

11:39.133 --> 11:41.875
but he's not
saying anything.

11:41.918 --> 11:44.791
You have to be careful.

11:44.834 --> 11:48.142
If Smurf thinks you're asking
too many questions, she will...

11:48.185 --> 11:50.100
I'm not afraid of Smurf.

11:52.146 --> 11:53.887
You should be.

11:55.018 --> 11:59.631
J, you deserve everything
she kept from you and Julia

11:59.675 --> 12:02.112
for all those years
and more.

12:02.156 --> 12:03.984
She might not even
have a will.

12:04.027 --> 12:06.682
[ Chuckles ] She probably thinks
she's gonna live forever.

12:06.726 --> 12:10.294
And if -- if there is one,
you're probably not in it.

12:10.338 --> 12:12.862
We need to get
what's yours.

12:12.906 --> 12:15.778
I can help you.

12:15.822 --> 12:17.171
Okay.

12:20.304 --> 12:22.393
We -- We need to move fast.
I'm going to work.

12:22.437 --> 12:23.873
Find out
where the money is.

12:23.917 --> 12:25.919
I don't think
she has long.

12:25.962 --> 12:32.012
♪♪

12:32.055 --> 12:38.366
♪♪

12:40.281 --> 12:41.804
Oh, hey, baby.

12:41.848 --> 12:43.414
Should I make you
some breakfast?

12:43.458 --> 12:46.374
Uh, no. Thank you.
Coffee's good.

12:48.376 --> 12:50.378
Do you have any information
for me?

12:50.421 --> 12:53.424
Nobody knows about anyone
talking to the police.

12:53.468 --> 12:56.863
I think it may be bullshit.It's not bullshit, J.

13:01.345 --> 13:03.130
[ Mug thuds ]

13:05.088 --> 13:08.222
I, uh,
have an idea for a job.

13:10.877 --> 13:13.314
Do you?

13:13.357 --> 13:16.665
There's this big concert
called the Chronic Dread Fest.

13:16.708 --> 13:19.755
20 acts.
14,000 people.

13:19.799 --> 13:22.236
I have an in
through this girl I know.

13:22.279 --> 13:26.457
It's good, but I'm not sure
what the best target is.

13:28.720 --> 13:32.072
Festival's been going on
for decades.

13:32.115 --> 13:34.465
Do they even have box offices
anymore?

13:34.509 --> 13:36.511
No. All the tickets
are online.

13:36.554 --> 13:40.254
But we have a way
into operations.

13:40.297 --> 13:42.082
Your girl.

13:42.125 --> 13:43.648
We could hit the acts.

13:43.692 --> 13:46.651
We could hit their equipment,
maybe some concessions.

13:46.695 --> 13:48.436
I can get
inventory lists

13:48.479 --> 13:50.960
for everything they bring
to their shows,

13:51.004 --> 13:53.789
everything they have
in their buses.

13:53.833 --> 13:56.618
What are we talking about?
Guitars?

13:56.661 --> 13:59.926
And electronics,
sound boards...

13:59.969 --> 14:02.450
That's pretty bulky.

14:02.493 --> 14:04.887
What are they worth?

14:04.931 --> 14:06.889
According to
the inventory lists,

14:06.933 --> 14:10.937
anywhere between 10 and 70K
depending on the size.

14:10.980 --> 14:15.071
And they're already in flight
cases, ready for transport.

14:15.115 --> 14:16.899
Then there's the buses.

14:16.943 --> 14:20.685
There's money, jewelry.

14:20.729 --> 14:23.906
I could take the boys
to scout it.

14:23.950 --> 14:26.474
You think it's good?

14:26.517 --> 14:28.432
I think it could be.

14:30.478 --> 14:34.874
I'll call my fence
tomorrow, baby.

14:34.917 --> 14:39.400
Could you call him today?
Is he local?

14:39.443 --> 14:42.882
It's a she.
And no, she's not.

14:45.580 --> 14:48.583
I, um, have an in
to scout it today.

14:48.626 --> 14:50.150
I'm not sure
I'll have it tomorrow.

14:50.193 --> 14:52.152
That's the only thing.

14:52.195 --> 14:57.940
♪♪

15:01.117 --> 15:01.944
Okay.

15:01.988 --> 15:03.511
[ Mug rattles ]

15:05.905 --> 15:06.993
J?

15:11.040 --> 15:15.958
Her name is Gia,
the fence.

15:16.002 --> 15:18.700
I'll let her know
you're coming today.

15:23.139 --> 15:24.184
Thank you, Smurf.

15:24.227 --> 15:25.968
Don't thank me.

15:26.012 --> 15:27.883
Just pay me my cut.

15:27.927 --> 15:33.933
♪♪

15:35.673 --> 15:37.023
[ Laughter,
indistinct conversations ]

15:37.066 --> 15:39.460
[ Thudding ]

15:41.000 --> 15:47.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

15:51.211 --> 15:53.604
Finish me! Oh!

15:53.648 --> 15:55.737
Tell my mother
I love her!

15:55.780 --> 15:58.218
[ Laughs ]
Nice one, Phoenix.

15:58.261 --> 16:00.742
What the hell's going on?

16:00.785 --> 16:03.049
Phoenix
just killed Jake.

16:03.092 --> 16:04.224
[ Laughter ]

16:04.267 --> 16:05.790
You look like
you could use some breakfast

16:05.834 --> 16:08.750
to soak up what's left
of last night.

16:08.793 --> 16:10.012
I'm fine.

16:10.056 --> 16:11.318
You don't look fine.

16:11.361 --> 16:14.538
It's nothing
I can't sleep off

16:14.582 --> 16:17.628
if it weren't so goddamn loud
in here.

16:17.672 --> 16:20.196
My mama taught me a recipe
for a hangover.

16:20.240 --> 16:23.112
If you can tolerate a raw egg,
I can have you right as rain.

16:23.156 --> 16:26.202
Is your girlfriend
hard of hearing?

16:26.246 --> 16:28.857
You got a problem,
Smurf?

16:30.293 --> 16:31.773
I hear fine.

16:31.816 --> 16:34.123
Colin, Jake?
Y'all want some bacon?

16:34.167 --> 16:36.038
Yes, please.

16:38.823 --> 16:40.912
Let's go outside
for a second.

16:44.264 --> 16:45.961
[ Door closes ]

16:46.005 --> 16:47.310
What the hell's wrong
with you?

16:47.354 --> 16:48.616
Are we running
a kindergarten?

16:48.659 --> 16:50.139
Look, Jake's just
letting the kid

16:50.183 --> 16:52.141
have a few days by the water
and a decent bed.

16:52.185 --> 16:54.187
I don't trust her.

16:54.230 --> 16:55.536
She's harmless, okay?

16:55.579 --> 16:57.016
No one's harmless.

16:57.059 --> 16:58.104
[ Laughs ]

16:58.147 --> 17:00.715
Not every woman
is like you, Janine.

17:00.758 --> 17:03.544
Most women want
what Pam wants.

17:03.587 --> 17:06.460
Someone to cook for
and to keep them warm at night

17:06.502 --> 17:08.810
and safe from
the big, bad wolf.

17:10.159 --> 17:11.813
All you know about her

17:11.856 --> 17:15.208
is that she works in a diner
off the highway

17:15.251 --> 17:17.252
and can make a pancake.

17:17.297 --> 17:19.560
Maybe Jake needs a pancake
right now

17:19.603 --> 17:21.257
and a little something extra

17:21.300 --> 17:23.694
after you dumped him
and got him shot.

17:23.738 --> 17:25.087
But what he doesn't need

17:25.131 --> 17:27.349
is you picking fights
with his girlfriend

17:27.394 --> 17:28.917
because you're jealous.

17:28.960 --> 17:33.617
♪♪

17:33.661 --> 17:35.837
If you think
I'm jealous,

17:35.880 --> 17:38.622
you're a worse judge
of character

17:38.666 --> 17:40.363
than I thought you were.

17:40.407 --> 17:47.153
♪♪

17:47.196 --> 17:53.420
♪♪

17:53.463 --> 17:56.423
Well, computers
and instruments

17:56.466 --> 17:58.860
require cleaning
and serial wipes,

17:58.903 --> 18:01.863
and you could just as easily
take those to a pawnshop.

18:01.906 --> 18:05.258
What I'd be most interested in
are the boards.

18:05.301 --> 18:06.346
Lighting and sound.

18:06.389 --> 18:08.696
You could get
almost full price,

18:08.739 --> 18:12.526
maybe even more if they did
any customizing.

18:12.569 --> 18:13.875
And you can do that?

18:13.918 --> 18:16.704
Yeah.
For my regular percentage.

18:16.747 --> 18:20.273
Tell Smurf when they come in,
I'll come to her.

18:20.316 --> 18:23.885
How much do you think we can get
for the boards?

18:23.928 --> 18:27.193
I'll talk about the numbers
with Smurf.

18:27.236 --> 18:29.064
She sent me.

18:30.979 --> 18:32.589
I looked through everything
she wanted me to,

18:32.633 --> 18:36.071
and I'll discuss the details
with her.

18:36.115 --> 18:39.292
Okay.
I just don't think that...

18:39.335 --> 18:41.076
You don't think what?

18:43.600 --> 18:44.688
Nothing.

18:44.732 --> 18:46.125
I'll pass on
that message.

18:46.168 --> 18:48.214
No.
Say what you were gonna say.

18:48.257 --> 18:50.738
No, it's not my place.

18:50.781 --> 18:53.697
But I'll tell her
what you said.

18:53.741 --> 18:56.222
What's going on?

18:56.265 --> 18:57.919
Is there heat on her?

18:57.962 --> 18:59.050
No.

18:59.094 --> 19:00.095
If there's anything
I should know...

19:00.139 --> 19:01.923
No, it's fine.
It's fine.

19:01.966 --> 19:03.403
She -- She's --
She's gonna be okay.

19:03.446 --> 19:05.970
She's tough.

19:06.014 --> 19:07.320
You know her.

19:07.363 --> 19:10.410
Nothing can take her out,
right?

19:10.453 --> 19:13.456
No, she'll --
she'll beat this thing.

19:15.328 --> 19:16.633
She's sick?

19:19.375 --> 19:21.551
She has cancer.

19:21.595 --> 19:23.466
But she doesn't
want anyone to know.

19:23.510 --> 19:28.297
♪♪

19:28.341 --> 19:34.695
If it's easier for her to
go through you, I can do that.

19:34.738 --> 19:37.219
Thank you.

19:37.263 --> 19:39.221
It was nice
meeting you.

19:39.265 --> 19:45.662
♪♪

19:49.840 --> 19:52.800
[ Laughing ] Wow.
Look at you guys.

19:52.843 --> 19:56.107
What's up, Angela?
Heard you were staying here.

19:56.151 --> 19:58.588
Yeah, I thought you were
only supposed to be here
for a couple days.

19:58.632 --> 20:02.288
Pope's letting me crash here
till I get on my feet.

20:02.331 --> 20:03.898
You got big, man.

20:03.941 --> 20:06.901
-Yeah.
-Is, uh, J around?

20:18.434 --> 20:20.349
Are you feeling okay?

20:26.399 --> 20:28.531
When's your next
chemo appointment?

20:28.575 --> 20:33.449
There won't be
a next chemo appointment.

20:33.493 --> 20:35.234
It wasn't for me.

20:39.716 --> 20:43.416
So, now what, huh?

20:43.459 --> 20:46.636
What happens --
I mean --

20:46.680 --> 20:48.508
I mean, do -- do --
do you need a nurse?

20:48.551 --> 20:51.989
Do you need a nurse
or something?

20:52.033 --> 20:55.123
What are we supposed to do
when...

20:55.166 --> 20:57.430
♪♪

20:57.473 --> 20:59.519
When what, baby?

20:59.562 --> 21:02.304
What are you gonna do
when what?

21:02.348 --> 21:06.700
♪♪

21:06.743 --> 21:10.530
J, take the margaritas outside
for me, please.

21:10.573 --> 21:12.314
Thank you, baby.

21:12.358 --> 21:16.710
♪♪

21:16.753 --> 21:18.886
Don't worry, Andrew.

21:18.929 --> 21:21.367
I won't leave you
with a mess.

21:21.410 --> 21:27.416
♪♪

21:28.635 --> 21:34.641
♪♪

21:36.120 --> 21:39.559
We're having a family meeting
now, Angela.

21:39.602 --> 21:41.517
Would you mind?

21:41.561 --> 21:47.306
♪♪

21:51.092 --> 21:53.921
Still got this shit
going on, huh?

21:53.964 --> 21:55.749
I'm surprised
you let her stay here.

21:55.792 --> 21:58.012
She keeps Pope calm.

22:01.276 --> 22:02.582
Okay, J.

22:02.625 --> 22:04.235
Put it on the table.

22:05.411 --> 22:07.761
You guys heard
of Chronic Dread Festival?

22:07.804 --> 22:09.458
Yeah,
I used to go every year

22:09.502 --> 22:11.591
before the, uh,
hipsters took it over.

22:11.634 --> 22:13.462
That's where Brenden lost
his eye in the mosh pit.

22:13.506 --> 22:15.682
He didn't lose his eye.
He just can't see out of it.

22:15.725 --> 22:17.597
It's the same shit.

22:17.640 --> 22:21.601
I can get us passes to park VIP
right near the loading docks.

22:21.644 --> 22:23.690
There are four
light and sound boards

22:23.733 --> 22:25.605
that the headliners use
backstage.

22:25.648 --> 22:27.476
Go for about 70K each.

22:27.520 --> 22:29.609
There's gonna be people
everywhere.

22:29.652 --> 22:30.871
What,
no one's gonna notice us

22:30.914 --> 22:32.438
just loading sound boards
onto a truck?

22:32.481 --> 22:34.788
200 people work at this event.
Nobody knows who's who.

22:34.831 --> 22:36.964
They don't have to knowus.
They have to seeus.

22:37.007 --> 22:40.533
Stuff goes missing, it takes
one guy who remembers us.

22:41.795 --> 22:43.797
What do you want us
to do?

22:43.840 --> 22:48.628
We gotta scout it today,
around 3:00 p.m.

22:48.671 --> 22:49.759
Alright.

22:50.456 --> 22:54.198
Come on.
This sounds like an easy job.

22:54.242 --> 22:56.897
Let's make this
a good one.

22:56.940 --> 22:59.943
Alright.
[ Clears throat ]

22:59.987 --> 23:01.989
Where are you going,
baby?

23:02.032 --> 23:03.382
I have some stuff to do.

23:03.425 --> 23:05.558
But if we have to
scout this thing later,

23:05.601 --> 23:07.255
I'll come meet you guys.

23:07.298 --> 23:08.561
Good.

23:12.521 --> 23:17.091
♪♪

23:17.134 --> 23:20.050
Hey.

23:20.094 --> 23:22.749
You might wanna
sit this one out.

23:22.792 --> 23:25.404
Why?
You know why.

23:25.447 --> 23:27.623
I'll be fine.
See you later.

23:27.667 --> 23:31.758
♪♪

23:31.801 --> 23:33.542
♪ When the gates of...♪

23:33.586 --> 23:36.110
How long are we gonna
stay here, Mama?

23:36.153 --> 23:39.853
Oh, not too much longer, baby.
You get some sleep.

23:41.507 --> 23:46.337
♪ I'll be happy
to go on living♪

23:46.381 --> 23:50.994
♪ Because my life
will never end♪

23:51.038 --> 23:52.474
You're smoking
that stuff a lot.

23:52.518 --> 23:55.172
Yeah, well, ever since
little Miss Pancakes

23:55.216 --> 23:57.566
has started cooking,
my stomach's been shit.

23:57.610 --> 24:00.221
♪ Managed through it all
somehow♪

24:00.264 --> 24:03.485
Colin,
how are you feeling, baby?

24:03.529 --> 24:04.704
I'm alright.

24:04.747 --> 24:06.270
Hmm, well.

24:06.314 --> 24:09.491
If the boys are doing alright,
I guess it isn't my cooking.

24:09.535 --> 24:16.629
♪♪

24:16.672 --> 24:17.586
[ Door closes ]

24:17.630 --> 24:19.327
Baby.

24:19.370 --> 24:22.722
♪♪

24:22.765 --> 24:24.288
So do you
hate all kids,

24:24.332 --> 24:25.725
or is there something special
about that one?

24:25.768 --> 24:28.031
It's his mom
I don't like.

24:28.075 --> 24:30.860
Ah,
'cause she's with Jake?

24:30.904 --> 24:35.343
No,
because she's with us.

24:35.386 --> 24:37.519
Hmm.

24:37.563 --> 24:40.261
Why would you
let your kid

24:40.304 --> 24:44.134
sleep in a house
with a bunch of thieves?

24:44.178 --> 24:46.528
Maybe she doesn't know.

24:46.572 --> 24:47.747
She knows.

24:47.790 --> 24:52.273
♪♪

24:52.316 --> 24:55.624
Not everyone's
out to get you.

24:55.668 --> 24:58.148
Okay. [ Laughs ]

25:01.500 --> 25:03.632
That's funny
coming from you.

25:03.676 --> 25:05.634
[ Both laughing ]

25:08.289 --> 25:10.552
I walked into that one.

25:10.596 --> 25:15.688
You like all of that, um,
"baby, sweetie, honey" shit?

25:19.648 --> 25:22.738
Good, 'cause I'm never
gonna do that.

25:24.131 --> 25:25.611
I like you.

25:25.654 --> 25:32.705
♪♪

25:32.748 --> 25:34.837
That help you relax?

25:34.881 --> 25:35.751
A little.

25:35.795 --> 25:39.015
Yeah, well, good.

25:39.059 --> 25:40.582
'Cause you need to.

25:40.626 --> 25:46.501
♪♪

25:46.545 --> 25:50.505
I just don't like us being
in one place for too long.

25:51.985 --> 25:55.249
You stop moving,
you get caught.

25:55.292 --> 25:56.424
Yeah.

25:56.467 --> 25:58.644
♪♪

25:58.687 --> 26:00.646
[ Gate rattling open ]

26:02.082 --> 26:03.692
Jennifer: Angela?

26:03.736 --> 26:05.172
Hey.

26:06.739 --> 26:07.957
When'd you get out?

26:08.001 --> 26:09.655
Ah, couple weeks ago.

26:09.698 --> 26:12.396
Didn't they get you
with a gun?

26:12.440 --> 26:15.269
I minded my business,
did what they said,

26:15.312 --> 26:16.705
and let me out early.

26:16.749 --> 26:18.838
Six years early?

26:18.881 --> 26:20.709
Did you roll
on someone?

26:21.928 --> 26:23.190
Oh, my God.

26:23.233 --> 26:25.758
This place looks
exactly the same.

26:25.801 --> 26:27.411
[ Laughs ]

26:27.455 --> 26:29.283
We did
some crazy shit here.

26:29.326 --> 26:31.807
[ Laughs ]
Wait till you see inside.

26:31.851 --> 26:34.593
[ Laughs ]

26:34.636 --> 26:35.811
Where's Smurf?

26:35.855 --> 26:39.075
I don't know.
She took off somewhere.

26:39.902 --> 26:41.556
[ Laughs ]

26:41.600 --> 26:43.819
Didn't you give your first
blow job in this kitchen?

26:43.863 --> 26:45.865
[ Laughs ]
It wasn't my first.

26:45.908 --> 26:48.041
Mm-hmm.

26:48.084 --> 26:50.217
Smurf let you
stay here?

26:50.260 --> 26:52.045
Wasn't up to her.
Pope let me stay.

26:52.088 --> 26:55.918
Oh. Is he still
crazy as hell?

26:55.962 --> 26:58.747
Misunderstood.
He's cool.

26:58.791 --> 27:01.532
What's he been up to?

27:01.576 --> 27:03.143
Same shit.

27:03.186 --> 27:06.407
He know
what you were in for?

27:06.450 --> 27:09.671
I told him it was a B&E.
I left out the gun part.

27:09.715 --> 27:11.020
Oh, smart.

27:11.064 --> 27:12.892
Can't imagine Smurf would
let there be two bitches

27:12.935 --> 27:14.458
in the house
who rob people.

27:14.502 --> 27:16.722
She doesn't want another woman
in the house at all.

27:16.765 --> 27:19.420
♪♪

27:19.463 --> 27:22.989
She doesn't have any pictures
of Julia.

27:23.032 --> 27:25.078
Yeah.

27:25.121 --> 27:27.689
They act like
she never existed.

27:27.733 --> 27:33.695
♪♪

27:36.916 --> 27:38.613
Smurf: Nice shot, Neal.

27:40.659 --> 27:42.878
Jesus, Smurf.

27:42.922 --> 27:44.227
You can't be here.

27:44.271 --> 27:46.099
Do you know how many cops
hang out here?

27:46.142 --> 27:47.709
If anyone sees you...

27:47.753 --> 27:49.929
Do you think you can drop
a piece of information

27:49.972 --> 27:52.018
like you did
and then just disappear?

27:52.061 --> 27:53.846
No, Neal.

27:53.889 --> 27:56.326
I don't have
anything new.

27:56.370 --> 27:58.633
How long we been doing this?
20 years?

27:58.677 --> 28:01.723
Don't I always give you
what I've got?

28:01.767 --> 28:03.420
No.

28:03.464 --> 28:07.207
You sure didn't keep up your end
of the deal when I was in jail.

28:07.250 --> 28:08.774
Your own kid set you up.

28:08.817 --> 28:11.820
What the hell was I
supposed to do about that?

28:11.864 --> 28:13.213
And it sure as shit
doesn't help

28:13.256 --> 28:15.650
that Pearce
has a hard-on for you.

28:15.694 --> 28:17.260
This is Pearce?

28:17.304 --> 28:19.480
Your secret admirer.

28:19.523 --> 28:21.830
And if anyone tells him
that they saw us talking,

28:21.874 --> 28:23.484
I can kiss my pension
goodbye.

28:23.527 --> 28:26.617
You think I give a shit
about your pension?

28:26.661 --> 28:30.273
Someone is talking
about my family.

28:30.317 --> 28:33.799
I want a name, Neal.

28:35.017 --> 28:37.977
I will ask around some more,
but you gotta go.

28:38.020 --> 28:39.630
I'll come by
the house later.

28:39.674 --> 28:41.937
I'm leaving town
for a few days.

28:41.981 --> 28:45.506
Make sure you have something
for me when I get back.

28:48.988 --> 28:54.907
♪♪

28:54.950 --> 29:01.261
♪♪

29:01.304 --> 29:02.523
That's the bullpen.

29:02.566 --> 29:04.090
I'll be in there
most of the day

29:04.133 --> 29:07.006
letting you know when the acts
and the security are moving.

29:07.049 --> 29:08.747
We'll have access
to all this?

29:08.790 --> 29:11.793
Yeah, your passes
give you access everywhere.

29:11.837 --> 29:13.969
Tour buses
will be back here?

29:14.013 --> 29:15.971
Yeah.

29:16.015 --> 29:18.800
There's gonna be lots of people.
We won't be able to wear masks.

29:18.844 --> 29:21.455
Well, everyone's busy.

29:21.498 --> 29:23.022
They'll be distracted.

29:23.065 --> 29:25.546
♪♪

29:25.589 --> 29:27.200
This is where
the sound boards will be.

29:27.243 --> 29:28.810
In place
for a quick turnaround.

29:28.854 --> 29:30.986
We'll look like staff.

29:31.030 --> 29:32.988
We'll be leaving
in traffic.

29:33.032 --> 29:37.645
If they notice they're gone,
we'll be sitting ducks.

29:41.910 --> 29:43.390
Cameras?

29:43.433 --> 29:46.872
No. Violates the artist
non-disclosure agreements.

29:46.915 --> 29:48.743
Tacara: Josh?

29:49.483 --> 29:52.834
Uh, these guys are looking
for the house electrician?

29:52.878 --> 29:55.445
Try the arena office.

29:55.489 --> 29:57.360
We have to finish
the bags.

29:57.404 --> 30:00.015
Oh, yeah.
Uh, I'm on my way.

30:00.059 --> 30:02.409
Uh, I think it's this --

30:04.063 --> 30:05.978
So, what do you think?

30:06.021 --> 30:07.370
I don't know, man.

30:07.414 --> 30:10.896
We gotta get out of here fast
if things go south.

30:10.939 --> 30:14.029
Deran: Can't we just take
the sound boards off the trucks

30:14.073 --> 30:14.900
before they unload them?

30:14.943 --> 30:17.380
It's riskier.

30:17.424 --> 30:20.079
The drivers, they wait
out by the trucks.

30:20.122 --> 30:22.516
Yeah, we're closer to an exit
by the trucks

30:22.559 --> 30:23.996
and we could hit
the buses, too.

30:24.039 --> 30:25.084
It's all
in one place.

30:25.127 --> 30:26.520
Yeah, we'll still
be in traffic.

30:26.563 --> 30:28.783
People are coming and going
from the festival all day.

30:28.827 --> 30:31.003
Yeah, it took us 40 minutes just
to get out of the parking lot

30:31.046 --> 30:32.743
when Brenden hit his eye.

30:32.787 --> 30:35.050
We finally had to give up
and call an ambulance.

30:35.094 --> 30:37.444
Why didn't you call an ambulance
in the first place?

30:37.487 --> 30:39.011
'Cause that shit costs 5K.

30:39.054 --> 30:43.058
Figured he'd lost his eye
anyway, so why waste the cash?

30:43.102 --> 30:45.539
Could we get an ambulance?

30:45.582 --> 30:47.541
They have backstage access.

30:47.584 --> 30:49.978
No one's gonna question an
ambulance leaving the concert.

30:50.022 --> 30:57.116
♪♪

30:57.159 --> 31:00.162
This place is nice.
You decorate it yourself?

31:00.206 --> 31:02.948
I did.
Hmm.

31:02.991 --> 31:06.168
You got all of this
from stealing shit, huh?

31:06.212 --> 31:07.604
No, baby.

31:07.648 --> 31:11.826
I got all of this
from being very smart.

31:11.870 --> 31:15.134
Well, I'd like a place like this
for my kid.

31:15.177 --> 31:16.962
I bet you would.

31:17.005 --> 31:21.096
Is that why you charged me
double this time?

31:21.140 --> 31:24.926
Home delivery.
Extra.

31:24.970 --> 31:27.233
You're a businesswoman.
You understand, Smurf.

31:27.276 --> 31:30.976
Bitch, I could get every one
of these weapons in Riverside

31:31.019 --> 31:32.020
at half the price.

31:32.064 --> 31:34.153
Well, then,
drive to Riverside.

31:34.196 --> 31:37.896
It's only a couple of hours
from here to there, right?

31:39.419 --> 31:43.510
These Glocks
only police can buy.

31:45.033 --> 31:47.079
You running a job?

31:47.122 --> 31:48.167
Hmm?

31:48.210 --> 31:50.082
This is some heavy artillery,
Smurf.

31:50.125 --> 31:53.172
What are you trying to do, take
out a whole town or something?

31:53.215 --> 31:55.130
Serial numbers
all wiped?

31:55.174 --> 31:58.307
Yes.
I double-checked.

31:59.918 --> 32:02.572
Why didn't you have your boys
come and get these, huh?

32:02.616 --> 32:04.531
It would've been cheaper.

32:04.574 --> 32:08.709
The boys don't need
to know everything, do they?

32:11.016 --> 32:13.714
No, they don't.

32:17.239 --> 32:19.938
Thank you.Drive safe, baby.

32:23.463 --> 32:24.812
[ Door closes ]

32:24.855 --> 32:26.422
Jake: Shit!

32:26.466 --> 32:28.947
Son of a bitch![ Clattering ]

32:31.123 --> 32:33.429
God damn it!

32:33.473 --> 32:35.649
What the hell's
going on?

32:35.692 --> 32:37.433
That bitch Pam
stole our money.

32:37.477 --> 32:39.609
How the hell did she know
where the money was?

32:39.653 --> 32:41.307
I don't know.You didn't see her leaving?!

32:41.350 --> 32:43.439
-I was asleep!
-What about the van?

32:43.483 --> 32:48.401
♪♪

32:48.444 --> 32:50.838
God damn it!

32:50.881 --> 32:56.713
♪♪

32:56.757 --> 32:58.193
What, you think
this is funny?

32:58.237 --> 33:05.244
♪♪

33:05.287 --> 33:06.810
Yo, I'm back.

33:06.854 --> 33:10.075
I got those, uh,
egg rolls you like.

33:10.118 --> 33:13.382
Two orders this time.
So you can have your own.

33:14.079 --> 33:15.384
Renn?

33:22.043 --> 33:28.006
♪♪

33:30.182 --> 33:36.188
♪♪

33:38.103 --> 33:44.109
♪♪

33:46.241 --> 33:52.247
♪♪

33:54.423 --> 34:00.429
♪♪

34:02.605 --> 34:06.435
[ Gearshift clicks,
engine shuts off ]

34:06.479 --> 34:12.485
♪♪

34:14.007 --> 34:20.014
♪♪

34:38.641 --> 34:40.730
Holy shit.

34:43.603 --> 34:44.603
[ Clears throat ]

34:44.647 --> 34:46.562
You're going somewhere.

34:49.130 --> 34:50.436
Deran know?

34:50.478 --> 34:52.873
No.
[ Clears throat ]

34:54.831 --> 34:56.833
Have you talked to him?

34:56.877 --> 34:59.749
No, not since
last night.

35:03.188 --> 35:04.189
Have you?

35:04.232 --> 35:10.891
♪♪

35:10.934 --> 35:13.546
If you do,
tell him I'm at my sister's.

35:13.589 --> 35:19.595
♪♪

35:22.120 --> 35:28.126
♪♪

35:34.132 --> 35:36.917
[ The Ginger Faye Bakers'
"Weekend Jeans" plays ]

35:36.960 --> 35:41.400
♪♪

35:41.443 --> 35:43.315
You told Adrian.

35:43.358 --> 35:44.707
What?

35:44.751 --> 35:47.188
You told him about Colby,
didn't you?

35:47.232 --> 35:48.842
That's why he's leaving.

35:48.885 --> 35:51.018
What do you mean,
he's leaving?

35:51.061 --> 35:53.281
I just left your place.
He's leaving.

